name: True Value
summary: True Value, a long-standing hardware chain based in Chicago, has filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy. The move comes after years of financial struggles for the company. True Value has announced plans to sell its business to Do It Best, a hardware rival. Do It Best has made a bid to acquire True Value's assets, including its retail stores and distribution centers. The sale is expected to be completed later this year. True Value's bankruptcy is the latest in a string of retail bankruptcies this year, highlighting the challenges faced by the industry amidst changing consumer shopping habits and increased competition from online retailers.

name: HSV-1
summary: Medical research and news headlines on viral infections and treatments: Researchers have engineered oncolytic HSV-1 viruses with IL-15/IL-15Rα complex and oncolytic HSV-1-aPD1 to enhance their antitumor effectiveness against colon cancer. Engineered HSV can trigger genetic chain reactions and rejigger HSV genes during co-infection, potentially aiding cancer treatment. A case study reports a patient developing tracheal rupture after intubation due to HSV-1 tracheitis. Scientists have uncovered the mechanism by which MX protein combats HIV-1 and herpes simplex virus. Cytoplasmic condensates have been shown to attract viruses, offering a potential new strategy for viral control. HSV's "talisman" is firing again in the context of soccer news. A lawsuit alleges that a musical artist exposed women to STDs. AXIN1 is found to enhance antiviral response through IRF3 stabilization and induced phase separation. A viral gene drive is proposed as a potential approach to fight herpes. Finally, an expert addresses concerns about a six-year-old child developing a cold sore and its potential implications for future outbreaks.

name: Europa Clipper
summary: NASA's Europa Clipper mission, launched by SpaceX's Falcon Heavy rocket, is on its way to Jupiter's moon, Europa. The historic mission aims to explore Europa, which is believed to harbor a vast subsurface ocean, potentially containing life. The Clipper will conduct detailed investigations of Europa's environment, composition, and interior structure to determine its habitability and search for signs of life. The mission will revolutionize our understanding of Jupiter's icy moon and its potential for supporting life beyond Earth.
